{0 API reference}

wodoc is both a command-line tool and an OCaml library. The library exposes one
module per pass of the {{!page-"overview"}pipeline}; the [wodoc] command-line
subcommands ({{!page-"commands"}Commands}) are thin wrappers over them.

{1 Modules}

{!modules:
Wodoc.Preprocess
Wodoc.Render
Wodoc.Assemble
Wodoc.Nav
Wodoc.Resolve
Wodoc.Convert
Wodoc.Config
Wodoc.Build
Wodoc.Blog
}

{1 Where to start}

- {!Wodoc.Preprocess} — rewrite [{%wodoc:…%}] markers to HTML-comment sentinels
  before odoc runs.
- {!Wodoc.Render} — turn those sentinels in odoc's HTML into real nested HTML.
- {!Wodoc.Assemble} — wrap the rendered HTML in a project's site template.
- {!Wodoc.Nav} — render a client/server project's API module list from a curated
  odoc index (the manual's own navigation is declared in the
  {{!page-"config"}[doc/wodoc] config}, not here).
- {!Wodoc.Resolve} — link cross-package "sibling" references odoc left dead.
- {!Wodoc.Convert} — the wikicréole → [.mld] migration aid.
- {!Wodoc.Config} — parse the declarative {{!page-"config"}[doc/wodoc]} file.
- {!Wodoc.Build} — the turn-key [wodoc build]: assemble a whole site from it.
- {!Wodoc.Blog} — the ultra-simple blog: dated [.mld] posts, a generated nav
  section and a "latest posts" landing fragment.
